ofessionals%20to%20teach%20their%20employees%20how%20to%20navigate%20interactions%20with%20VIP%20clients%20at%20formal%20events%20smoothly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%2C%20according%20to%20Jamila%20Musayeva%2C%20an%20etiquette%20coach%2C%20is%20to%20avoid%20standing%20out%20as%20new%20money%20or%20someone's%20plus-one%20when%20attending%20fancy%20dinners%20or%20galas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fjv_y-DQGGEQ%3Fsi%3DSB-iQPsw6t__Nowv%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Musayeva%2C%20who's%20often%20hired%20to%20coach%20people%20for%20black-%20or%20white-tie%20events%2C%20as%20well%20as%20general%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-hiring-etiquette-coaches-to-help-rto-workers-behavior-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebusiness%20etiquette%20training%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20best%20indication%20that%20your%20etiquette%20is%20up%20to%20par%20is%20if%20your%20behavior%20goes%20unnoticed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20one%20cannot%20pinpoint%20what%20you%20were%20doing%20at%20the%20table%2C%20then%20you%20had%20it%20all%20mastered%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20all%20hopefully%20learned%20basic%20table%20manners%20over%20the%20years%2C%20but%20the%20wealthy%20take%20etiquette%20to%20another%20level%20for%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmet-gala-co-chairs-theme-dress-code-explained-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elavish%20gala%20dinners%20and%20social%20happenings%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20Musayeva's%20etiquette%20do's%20and%20don'ts%20at%20exclusive%20events%20frequented%20by%20the%20wealthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDON'T%3A%20Discuss%20your%20dietary%20restrictions%20or%20preferences%20at%20the%20table.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20your%20local%20diner%2C%20so%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20alert%20your%20servers%20of%20allergies%20while%20seated.%20Musayeva%20told%20BI%20that%20it's%20common%20for%20gala%20dinners%20to%20include%20an%20option%20to%20disclose%20any%20restrictions%20when%20you%20RSVP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20way%2C%20everyone%20can%20avoid%20an%20awkward%20dietary%20conversation%20at%20the%20table.%20Such%20luxurious%20events%20should%20already%20account%20for%20any%20special%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EPractice%20the%20continental%20way%20of%20eating.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrying-a-1000-royal-etiquette-class-at-the-plaza-hotel-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtinental%20dining%20style%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20considered%20common%20ground%20for%20people%20from%20different%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20%26quot%3Bholding%20the%20fork%20in%20the%20left%20hand%20and%20knife%20in%20the%20right%20hand%20without%20switching%C2%A0them%20back%20and%20forth%20as%20you%20would%20do%20in%20American-style%20eating.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20typically%20use%20their%20knives%20and%20forks%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bzig-zag%26quot%3B%20way%2C%20said%20Musayeva%2C%20but%20that's%20seen%20as%20informal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDON'T%3A%20Take%20a%20sip%20of%20your%20drink%20before%20you've%20finished%20chewing.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20one%20is%20pretty%20simple%3A%20take%20small%20bites%20of%20your%20food%20and%20finish%20chewing%20and%20swallowing%20before%20you%20drink%20your%20beverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDO%3A%20Leave%20your%20big%20handbag%20in%20the%20coat%20closet.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20room%20at%20the%20table%20of%20esteemed%20guests%20for%20your%20bulky%20shoulder%20bag%2C%20so%20it's%20best%20to%20leave%20it%20at%20coat%20check.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you'd%20rather%20not%20ditch%20your%20belongings%2C%20Musayeva%20suggests%20accessorizing%20with%20a%20smaller%20purse%20that%20fits%20in%20your%20lap%20when%20it's%20time%20for%20dinner%20to%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20recommend%20always%20to%20take%20a%20clutch%20or%20a%20small%20black%20bag%20that%20you%20can%20then%20place%20in%20your%20lap%20and%20cover%20it%20with%20a%20napkin%2C%26quot%3B%20Musayeva%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDON'T%3A%20Introduce%20your%20VIP%20guest%20%3Cem%3Eto%20%3C%2Fem%3Esomeone.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20first%20impressions%2C%20you%20should%20always%20make%20sure%20the%20VIP's%20status%20is%20discreetly%20acknowledged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20such%2C%20you%20should%20never%20introduce%20them%20%3Cem%3Eto%20%3C%2Fem%3Esomeone%20%E2%80%94%20everyone%20should%20already%20know%20who%20they%20are%2C%20so%20it's%20unnecessary.%20Instead%2C%20Musayeva%20said%2C%20you%20should%20introduce%20people%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20say%20this%20formula%3A%20'May%20I%20introduce%20to%20you'%26quot%3B%20and%20then%20the%20name%2C%20Musayeva%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDO%3A%20Let%20the%20VIP%20guest%20decide%20when%20to%20shake%20hands.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20want%20to%20make%20an%20honored%20guest%20feel%20welcomed%20by%20extending%20a%20hand%20to%20them%20as%20a%20greeting.%20But%2C%20Musayeva%20said%2C%20that's%20not%20the%20proper%20way%20to%20go%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20hierarchical%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20most%20important%20person%20has%20to%20give%20permission%20to%20a%20less%20important%20person%20to%20shake%20their%20hand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDON'T%3A%20Order%20your%20own%20drink%20at%20the%20dinner%20table.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20formal%20dinners%2C%20drink%20pairings%20are%20usually%20predetermined%20to%20match%20the%20food%20on%20the%20menu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20come%20off%20as%20rude%20if%20you%20object%20to%20the%20wine%20or%20other%20drink%20chosen%20by%20your%20host%20or%20chef%2C%20Musayeva%20said.%20It's%20better%20to%20trust%20their%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECocktail%20hour%20is%20the%20best%20time%20to%20order%20whatever%20beverage%20you're%20craving%2C%20but%20that%20ends%20once%20you%20sit%20down%20for%20dinner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDO%3A%20Whatever%20it%20takes%20to%20fit%20in.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFitting%20in%20is%20key.%20That%20means%20matching%20the%20etiquette%20of%20your%20host%20or%20the%20most%20important%20person%20at%20the%20table%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20they're%20straying%20away%20from%20the%20guidelines%20Musayeva%20teaches%20her%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20best%20to%20be%20observant%20and%20pick%20up%20on%20how%20everyone%20else%20behaves%20to%20understand%20how%20to%20interact%20appropriately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20they're%20all%20humans%2C%26quot%3B%20Musayeva%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20feel%20like%20lesser%20than%20them%2C%20your%20body%20language%20will%20tell%20them%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-fit-in-at-dinner-with-billionaire-vip-etiquette-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711530002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66025fac1caec1275a695303%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-fit-in-at-dinner-with-billionaire-vip-etiquette-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20very%20wealthy%20go%20by%20a%20specific%20set%20of%20manners.%20Etiquette%20coach%20Jamila%20Musayeva%20gives%20her%20tips%20for%20how%20to%20fit%20in%20at%20dinner%20with%20a%20billionaire.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jhart%40insider.com%20(Jordan%20Hart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.c