0Hanbury%20at%20Houghton%20Hall%20on%20June%2022%2C%202016.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f2ffe53037f8e817504aad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPrince%20William%2C%20Kate%20Middleton%2C%20and%20Rose%20Hanbury%20at%20Houghton%20Hall%20on%20June%2022%2C%202016.%3Cp%3EStephen%20Pond%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.georginasturmer.co.uk%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGeorgina%20Sturmer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20psychotherapist%20in%20the%20UK%20who%20specializes%20in%20relationships%2C%20also%20said%20that%20people's%20reaction%20to%20affair%20rumors%20and%20their%20willingness%20to%20believe%20it%20was%20behind%20Kate's%20absence%20demonstrates%20a%20sensitivity%20to%20the%20concept%20of%20cheating%20in%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20said%20people%20may%20have%20felt%20particularly%20triggered%20by%20the%20prospect%20of%20a%20royal%20cheating%20scandal%20because%20they%20have%20formed%20%26quot%3Bparasocial%20relationships%26quot%3B%20with%20Kate%20and%20William%2C%20meaning%20they%20feel%20like%20they%20know%20them%20even%20though%20they%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20build%20these%20parasocial%20relationships%20based%20on%20a%20sense%20of%20trust%20that%20we%20think%20we%20know%20someone.%20We%20think%20we%20know%20they%20are%20trustworthy%20and%20well-behaved%2C%20and%20they%20do%20all%20the%20right%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20rumor%20of%20infidelity%20starts%20going%20around%2C%20Sturmer%20also%20said%20people%20%26quot%3Binstinctively%26quot%3B%20resent%20and%20blame%20the%20other%20woman%20in%20the%20equation%20rather%20than%20the%20unfaithful%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can't%20cope%20with%20the%20idea%20that%20someone%20we%20imagine%20to%20be%20perfect%20or%20who%20we%20imagine%20to%20be%20a%20certain%20way%20could%20let%20us%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBlaming%20the%20'other%20woman'%20has%20always%20been%20society's%20coping%20mechanism%2C%20experts%20said%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20she%20has%20denied%20the%20rumors%2C%20Hanbury%20is%20still%20the%20latest%20example%20of%20how%20society%20has%20historically%20reacted%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bother%20woman%2C%26quot%3B%20Sturmer%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20it%20comes%20from%20how%20we've%20been%20%26quot%3Bwired%20to%20think%26quot%3B%20of%20women%20as%20cunning%20temptresses%20for%20millennia%2C%20citing%20Adam%20and%20Eve's%20story%20in%20the%20Bible%20as%20an%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20idea%20of%20women%20being%20vilified%20for%20being%20different%20or%20for%20trying%20to%20pull%20people%20into%20their%20way%20in%20a%20way%20that%20we%20excuse%20men%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20Sturmer%2C%20giving%20the%20American%20witch%20hunts%20of%20the%2017th%20century%20as%20another%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20she%20said%2C%20men%20have%20historically%20been%20painted%20as%20unwitting%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELundquist%20pointed%20to%20the%20popular%20Broadway%20show%20%26quot%3BSix%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20about%20Henry%20VIII's%20six%20wives%2C%20including%20Anne%20Boleyn%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20famous%20%26quot%3Bother%20women%26quot%3B%20in%20royal%20history%20%E2%80%94%20as%20an%20example%20of%20how%20%26quot%3Bother%20women%26quot%3B%20tend%20to%20be%20characterized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20show%20retells%20the%20wives'%20histories%20through%20the%20lens%20of%20%26quot%3Bempowerment%2C%26quot%3B%20Lundquist%20said%2C%20the%20characters%20are%20still%20%26quot%3Bcompetitive%26quot%3B%20and%20sometimes%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edisplay%20animosity%20toward%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20highlights%20how%20even%20in%20%26quot%3Bsomething%20that%20is%20presumptively%20feminist%20and%20redemptive%2C%26quot%3B%20society%20can't%20help%20but%20slip%20into%20a%20kind%20of%20%26quot%3Bhatred%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Bother%20woman.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20'other%20woman'%20label%20is%20nearly%20impossible%20to%20shake%20off%2C%20therapists%20said%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EReactions%20to%20Hanbury%20mirror%20the%20way%20people%20viewed%20and%20spoke%20about%20Camilla%20in%20the%201990s%20after%20her%20affair%20with%20King%20Charles%20while%20he%20was%20married%20to%20Princess%20Diana%20came%20to%20light.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Sturmer%2C%20it%20shows%20people%20can%20%26quot%3Bretreat%26quot%3B%20to%20basic%20stereotypes%20of%20men%20and%20women%20when%20the%20topic%20of%20sex%20arises%2C%20even%20if%20they%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20mean%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20though%20we're%20really%20enlightened%2C%20and%20we're%20really%20modern%2C%20and%20we're%20really%20feminist%2C%20and%20we%20know%20whose%20marriages%20have%20broken%20down%20and%20who%20have%20remarried%20and%20found%20love%2C%20despite%20all%20of%20that%2C%20we%20are%20still%20so%20conditioned%20by%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20Camilla%20has%20been%20married%20to%20Charles%20for%20nearly%20two%20decades%2C%20Sturmer%20also%20said%20she%20will%20always%20be%20associated%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bother%20woman.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYes%2C%20we%20have%20normalized%20her%2C%20we%20have%20humanized%20her%2C%20but%20she%20is%20still%20and%20always%20will%20have%20that%20label%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Queen%20Camilla%20and%20King%20Charles%20had%20a%20relationship%20while%20he%20was%20married%20to%20Princess%20Diana.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6601dcca16bde8d4ead1ffac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EQueen%20Camilla%20and%20King%20Charles%20had%20a%20relationship%20while%20he%20was%20married%20to%20Princess%20Diana.%3Cp%3EExpress%20Newspapers%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELundquist%20also%20said%20the%20ease%20with%20which%20people%20were%20quick%20to%20associate%20Hanbury%20with%20the%20%26quot%3Bother%20woman%26quot%3B%20trope%20demonstrates%20how%20pervasive%20misogyny%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20case%20of%20both%20Camilla%20and%20Rose%2C%20the%20bad%20object%20in%20these%20instances%20is%20a%20woman%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Once%20again%2C%20he%20said%20it's%20the%20%26quot%3Bsneaky%20conniving%20woman%26quot%3B%20who%20can%20trick%20a%20man%20and%20render%20him%20%26quot%3Bnot%20responsible%20for%20his%20decision-making%20in%20that%20process.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20he%20said%20people%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bright%20to%20feel%20bad%26quot%3B%20when%20cheating%20happens%20in%20monogamous%20relationships%2C%20it's%20the%20%26quot%3Bother%20woman%26quot%3B%20who%20often%20ends%20up%20carrying%20the%20greater%20burden%20because%20they%20are%20both%20%26quot%3Bother%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bwoman.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20hear%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20mom%20at%20the%20elementary%20school%20that%20gets%20scorned%20at%20drop-off%20because%20she%20had%20some%20kind%20of%20role%20in%20something%20like%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Lundquist%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20can%20be%20some%20real%20unkindness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESturmer%20wasn't%20surprised%20that%20the%20rumor%20of%20infidelity%20became%20a%20leading%20theory%20social%20media%20users%20put%20forward%20to%20explain%20what%20was%20going%20on%20with%20Kate%2C%20especially%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Egiven%20the%20royal%20family's%20history%20of%20cheating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20kind%20of%20the%20soap%20opera%20of%20our%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20stories%20that%20gain%20momentum%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20pull%20on%20those%20base%20urges%20that%20we%20have.%20It%20was%20almost%20like%20people%20were%20excited%20by%20this%20story%20%E2%80%94%20they%20wanted%20to%20believe%20something%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-people-quick-to-label-rose-hanbury-the-other-woman-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711520341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66019dce3f923f7dab00d94c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-people-quick-to-label-rose-hanbury-the-other-woman-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Experts%20weigh%20in%20on%20why%20unsubstantiated%20rumors%20that%20Prince%20William%20had%20an%20affair%20flourished%20as%20a%20reason%20for%20Kate%20Middleton's%20absence%20from%20the%20public%20eye.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mnoyen%40insider.com%20(Maria%20Noyen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A129%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-people-quick-to-label-rose-hanbury-the-other-woman-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Afridi's%20Blunt%20Message%20To%20PCB%20On%20Son-In-Law%20Shaheen's%20Likely%20Sacking%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFormer%20Pakistan%20skipper%20Shahid%20Afridi%20has%20come%20out%20in%20defence%20of%20his%20son-in-law%20Shaheen%20Shah%20Afridi%20following%20speculation%20that%20the%20tall%20pace%20bowler%20was%20going%20to%20be%20removed%20as%20the%20national%20T20%20captain.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20if%20you%20have%20appointed%20someone%20as%20captain%20(Shaheen)%20and%20given%20him%20the%20responsibility%20then%20give%20him%20time%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Afridi%20told%20the%20media%20on%20Tuesday.%20%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20problem%20with%20our%20cricket%20is%20that%20our%20system%20changes%20whenever%20the%20faces%20change%20in%20the%20board.%20Whoever%20comes%20thinks%20whatever%20he%20is%20doing%20is%20the%20best%20for%20Pakistan%20cricket%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Afridi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfridi%20remarked%20that%20Shaheen%20should%20be%20given%20adequate%20time%20to%20prove%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20change%20the%20captain%20then%20either%20the%20decision%20to%20appoint%20him%20was%20wrong%20or%20the%20decision%20to%20change%20him%20now%20is%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfridi%20was%20seen%20as%20one%20of%20the%20main%20driving%20forces%20behind%20the%20appointment%20of%20Shaheen%20as%20the%20national%20T20%20captain%20after%20last%20year's%20ODI%20World%20Cup%20India.%20Babar%20Azam%20was%20removed%20as%20the%20white-ball%20captain%20after%20Pakistan%20failed%20to%20advance%20beyond%20the%20league%20stages.%20The%20skipper%20then%20stepped%20down%20in%20the%20red-ball%20format.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfridi%20also%20backed%20the%20appointment%20of%20a%20foreign%20coach%20but%20said%20he%20should%20be%20a%20high-profile%20person%20like%20Andy%20Flower%2C%20who%20has%20a%20great%20track%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20believe%20that%20even%20if%20you%20bring%20in%20a%20foreign%20coach%2C%20the%20staff%20under%20him%20should%20be%20Pakistani%20so%20that%20our%20people%20can%20also%20move%20forward%20and%20improve%20their%20skills%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20decision%20to%20include%20Imad%20Wasim%20and%20Muhammad%20Amir%20in%20the%20national%20training%20camp%2C%20Afridi%20felt%20it%20would%20have%20been%20better%20to%20first%20assess%20their%20fitness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20I%20can%20tell%20you%20that%20if%20they%20can%20come%20through%20this%20two-week%20training%20camp%20in%20Kakul%20they%20will%20be%20supermen%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmir%2C%20back%20from%20retirement%20after%202020%2C%20has%20also%20backed%20Shaheen%20as%20T20%20captain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20tweeted%2C%20%26quot%3BShaheen%20is%20not%20bad%20and%20I%20think%20he%20should%20be%20given%20time%20to%20prove%20his%20credentials.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2