3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20cargo%20ship%20crashed%20into%20Baltimore's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffrancis-scott-key-bridge-baltimore-collapses-after-struck-large-boat-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFrancis%20Scott%20Key%20Bridge%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20caused%20it%20to%20collapse%2C%20shipments%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20Port%20of%20Baltimore%20could%20be%20blocked%20for%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaltimore-bridge-collapse-cargo-ship-mayday-call-traffic-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDali%20container%20ship%3C%2Fa%3E%20collided%20with%20one%20of%20the%20bridge's%20support%20beams%20early%20Tuesday%20morning%2C%20causing%20large%20portions%20of%20the%201.6-mile%20bridge%20to%20collapse%20into%20the%20Patapsco%20River%2C%20with%20the%20wreckage%20effectively%20blocking%20ships%20from%20moving%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20Port%20of%20Baltimore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbigger-ships-making-shipping-incidents-baltimore-bridge-more-complicated-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eport%20is%20currently%20closed%20to%20vessels%3C%2Fa%3E%20until%20further%20notice%2C%20with%20officials%20saying%20it's%20unclear%20when%20it%20will%20be%20able%20to%20reopen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndustry%20experts%20say%20it%20could%20take%20months%20and%20that%20an%20extended%20disruption%20could%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaltimore-port-closure-could-cost-15-million-per-day-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emajor%20economic%20consequences%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20direct%20impacts%20on%20the%20port's%20biggest%20imports%20and%20exports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20port%20is%20closed%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20impact%20all%20of%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Daraius%20Irani%2C%20chief%20economist%20for%20the%20Regional%20Economic%20Studies%20Institute%20at%20Towson%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20biggest%20point%20of%20entry%20for%20imported%20cars%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Port%20of%20Baltimore%20is%20the%20top%20port%20in%20the%20US%20for%20roll-on%2Froll-off%20cargo%2C%20which%20refers%20to%20wheeled%20cargo%20like%20vehicles%2C%20construction%20equipment%2C%20and%20agriculture%20equipment%2C%20according%20to%20the%20port.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20the%20port%20handled%20847%2C158%20automobiles%20and%20light%20trucks%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20any%20other%20US%20port%20for%20the%20thirteenth%20straight%20year%20%E2%80%94%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmsa.maryland.gov%2Fmsa%2Fmdmanual%2F01glance%2Fhtml%2Fport.html%23cargo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%20from%20the%20Port%20of%20Baltimore%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBaltimore%20is%20relatively%20unique%20in%20having%20the%20infrastructure%20to%20accept%20the%20cars%20and%20to%20store%20them%20until%20they%20ultimately%20reach%20their%20final%20destination%2C%26quot%3B%20Anirban%20Basu%2C%20economist%2C%20founder%2C%20and%20CEO%20of%20Baltimore-based%20Sage%20Policy%20Group%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoll-on%2Froll-off%20cargo%20is%20especially%20difficult%20to%20divert%20to%20other%20ports%2C%20in%20part%20because%20it%20generally%20takes%20up%20a%20lot%20of%20space%20and%20requires%20specific%20handling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeneral%20Motors%20told%20BI%20that%20it%20expects%20the%20collapse%20to%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bminimal%20impact%26quot%3B%20on%20their%20operations.%20%26quot%3BOur%20thoughts%20are%20with%20those%20who%20were%20affected%20and%20the%20Baltimore%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20working%20to%20re-route%20any%20vehicle%20shipments%20to%20other%20ports%20as%20the%20recovery%20work%20continues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20from%20Ford%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWhere%20workarounds%20are%20necessary%2C%20our%20team%20has%20already%20secured%20shipping%20alternatives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Port%20of%20Baltimore%20said%20it%20handled%201.3%20million%20tons%20of%20imported%20roll-on%2Froll-off%20cargo%20in%202023%2C%20including%20heavy%20farm%20and%20construction%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBasu%20said%20Caterpillar%2C%20a%20maker%20of%20construction%2C%20mining%2C%20and%20agricultural%20equipment%2C%20also%20moves%20much%20of%20its%20product%20through%20the%20Port%20of%20Baltimore.%20Caterpillar%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aerial%20shot%20of%20the%20Port%20of%20Baltimore%20at%20sunset%2C%20looking%20across%20and%20intermodal%20container%20yard%20towards%20a%20ship%20being%20unloaded%20by%20cranes.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660365d516bde8d4ead278d5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Port%20of%20Baltimore%20is%20the%20top%20US%20port%20for%20roll-on%2Froll-off%20cargo%2C%20like%20cars%20and%20construction%20machinery.%3Cp%3Ehalbergman%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3ECoal%2C%20gypsum%2C%20and%20sugar%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20coal%20was%20among%20the%20top%20export%20commodities%20by%20weight%20moved%20through%20the%20Port%20of%20Baltimore.%20In%202023%2C%20the%20port%20ranked%20second%20in%20the%20US%20for%20coal%20exports%2C%20according%20to%20the%20port.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Port%20of%20Baltimore%2C%20over%20time%2C%20has%20developed%20the%20ability%20to%20store%20and%20then%20load%20coal%20onto%20ships%20and%20have%20those%20ships%20go%20places%20long%20and%20far%2C%20including%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20Basu%20said%2C%20noting%20Maryland's%20proximity%20to%20West%20Virginia%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoal-magnate-building-renewable-energy-plant-size-chicago-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoal%20country%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20tons%20of%20coal%20are%20set%20not%20to%20be%20sent%20abroad%20in%20the%20near%20term%20as%20the%20port%20suffers%20this%20lack%20of%20operability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20the%20Port%20of%20Baltimore%20was%20also%20the%20top%20US%20port%20for%20imported%20gypsum%2C%20a%20mineral%20commonly%20used%20in%20fertilizer%20and%20construction%20material%2C%20and%20imported%20sugar%2C%20according%20to%20the%20port%2C%20which%20has%20a%20Domino%20Sugar%20refinery%20operating%20nearby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EASR%20Group%2C%20whose%20companies%20include%20Domino%20Sugar%20and%20C%26amp%3BH%20Sugar%2C%20told%20BI%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement%20they%20do%20not%20expect%20any%20short-term%20impacts%20to%20their%20operations%20in%20Baltimore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Baltimore%20Refinery%20has%20six%20to%20eight%20weeks%20of%20raw%20sugar%20supply%20on%20hand%20with%20a%20ship%20currently%20discharging%20at%20the%20refinery's%20dock%20and%20another%20that%20finished%20unloading%20on%20Monday%2C%20March%2025%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%20%26quot%3BASR%20Group%20also%20owns%20a%20network%20of%20production%20facilities%20and%20warehouses%20across%20the%20US%20that%20all%20currently%20have%20healthy%20inventories%20of%20finished%20products%20and%20can%20be%20utilized%20if%20necessary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPaper%2C%20chocolate%2C%20and%20ice%20cream%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20other%20items%20pass%20through%20the%20port%20every%20day.%20According%20to%20the%20port%2C%20in%202022%2C%20that%20included%201%2C000%20tons%20of%20aircraft%20and%20parts%2C%20793%2C695%20tons%20of%20paper%2C%2024%2C900%20tons%20of%20chocolate%2C%20and%20%2459.4%20million%20worth%20of%20ice%20cream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20444%2C000%20cruise%20ship%20passengers%20also%20departed%20from%20the%20terminal%20at%20the%20Port%20of%20Baltimore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20much%20the%20port%20closure%20will%20impact%20each%20of%20these%20industries%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%20%26quot%3BIt%20really%20just%20depends%20on%20how%20much%20stuff%20was%20there%20before%20this%20accident%20happened%2C%26quot%3B%20economist%20Irani%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20research%20briefing%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oxfordeconomics.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FThe-economic-costs-of-the-Key-Bridge-collapse.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOxford%20Economics%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20the%20bridge%20collapse%20will%20likely%20have%20a%20greater%20impact%20on%20the%20local%20Baltimore%20economy%20than%20on%20a%20national%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20will%20likely%20be%20some%20temporary%20disruptions%20to%20certain%20industries%2C%20including%20automakers%2C%20but%20nothing%20that%20warrants%20an%20immediate%20change%20to%20our%20baseline%20forecast%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20briefing%20said.%20%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20the%20duration%20of%20the%20disruptions%20at%20the%20Port%20of%20Baltimore%2C%20along%20with%20how%20quickly%20trade%20can%20be%20rerouted%2C%20will%20determine%20the%20economic%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaltimore-bridge-collapse-impact-imports-exports-cars-coal-farm-equipment-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711505301000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6603655c3f923f7dab018a79%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaltimore-bridge-collapse-impact-imports-exports-cars-coal-farm-equipment-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20bridge%20collapse%20has%20blocked%20shipments%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20Port%20of%20Baltimore%2C%20which%20handles%20a%20high%20volume%20of%20car%20imports%20and%20coal%20exports.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis%2CDominick%20Reuter)%22%2C%22enga