ltimore%2C%20Maryland%2C%20on%20March%2026%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660324a51caec1275a69b212%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221152%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDrone%20footage%20shows%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Dali%20container%20ship's%20collision%20into%20the%20Francis%20Scott%20Key%20Bridge%20in%20Baltimore%2C%20Maryland%2C%20on%20March%2026%2C%202024.%3Cp%3EAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Reuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20principle%20dates%20back%20hundreds%20of%20years%20and%20was%20originally%20meant%20to%20ensure%20sailors%20on%20board%20a%20ship%20weren't%20worried%20about%20specific%20cargo%20if%20a%20disaster%20required%20them%20to%20start%20throwing%20containers%20overboard%2C%20according%20to%20Petersen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20will%20pay%20for%20everything%20else%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20of%20the%20financial%20fallout%20is%20likely%20to%20lay%20primarily%20with%20the%20insurance%20industry%2C%20according%20to%20media%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndustry%20experts%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F17cf3f2e-e64d-4666-b1c2-2723347c2ada%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFT%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20insurers%20could%20pay%20out%20losses%20for%20bridge%20damage%2C%20port%20disruption%2C%20and%20any%20loss%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20collapse%20could%20drive%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20largest%20claims%20ever%20to%20hit%20the%20marine%20(re)insurance%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20Miklus%2C%20president%20of%20the%20American%20Institute%20of%20Marine%20Underwriters%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insurancebusinessmag.com%2Fus%2Fnews%2Fmarine%2Fmajor-reinsurers-and-pandi-club-on-hook-for-baltimore-bridge-disaster-482812.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInsurance%20Business.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20the%20outlet%20that%20the%20loss%20of%20revenue%20from%20tolls%20while