3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022-23%2C%20the%20FDI%20growth%20declined%20by%2016%25%20to%20%2471%20billion%20compared%20to%20a%203%25%20increase%20to%20%2485%20billion%20in%20the%20previous%20year.%20In%20the%20current%20financial%20year%20till%20December%202023%2C%20the%20FDI%20in%20form%20of%20equity%20inflow%20was%2013%25%20lower%20y-o-y%20to%20%2432%20billion%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20finance%20ministry%20acknowledged%20this%20issue%2C%20attributing%20the%20dip%20in%20FDI%20inflows%20to%20a%20global%20slowdown%20and%20a%20rise%20in%20repatriation%20of%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20slowdown%20in%20FDI%20growth%20is%20not%20a%20recent%20phenomenon.%20The%20slowdown%20has%20been%20setting%20in%20since%202016-17.%20In%20the%2010-year%20period%20to%202022-23%2C%20the%20FDI%20grew%20at%20a%20CAGR%20of%206.6%25%20compared%20to%2027%25%20in%20the%20previous%2010-year%20period.%20The%20FDI%20(equity%20inflow%2C%20reinvested%20earnings%20and%20other%20inflows%20put%20together)%20as%20a%20percentage%20of%20nominal%20GDP%20in%202022-23%20was%202.1%25%20compared%20to%202.7%25%20in%202021-22.%20The%20highest%20that%20India%20ever%20achieved%20was%203.5%25%20in%202008-09.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%202020-21%20saw%20India%E2%80%99s%20FDI%2FGDP%20ratio%20touching%203.1%25%20largely%20due%20to%20contraction%20in%20GDP%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%20April%20and%20September%20of%20last%20year%2C%20India%20received%20a%20little%20over%20%2410%20billion%20in%20FDI%20%E2%80%93%20the%20lowest%20figure%20for%20the%20first%20half%20of%20a%20financial%20year%20since%20the%202008%20global%20recession%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthediplomat.com%2F2024%2F03%2Findia-suffering-a-quiet-decline-in-foreign-direct-investment%2F%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhy-fdi-in-india-is-lowest-in-16-yrs-no-real-ease-of-doing-business-ill-considered-treaty-moves%2F1927937%2F%5C%22%3ERBI.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhy-fdi-in-india-is-lowest-in-16-yrs-no-real-ease-of-doing-business-ill-considered-treaty-moves%2F1927937%2F%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Print%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20%E2%80%98rigidities%E2%80%99%20in%20doing%20business%20here%2C%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20terminate%20bilateral%20treaties%20are%20to%20blame.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20factors%20why%20foreign%20investment%20into%20India%20has%20been%20so%20tepid%20in%20recent%20years%20include%20bureaucratic%20red%20tape%2C%20a%20poor%20record%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fopinion%2Fcontract-enforcement-key-to-ease-of-doing-business%2Farticle65238080.ece%5C%22%3Econtract%20enforcement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20relatively%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F09%2F29%2Findias-labor-force-continues-to-lags-behind-chinas-study-.html%5C%22%3Elow%20labour%20productivity%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthediplomat.com%2F2024%2F03%2Findia-suffering-a-quiet-decline-in-foreign-direct-investment%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDiplomat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20further%20attributes%20another%20factor%3A%20India%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20been%20signing%20enough%20deals%20to%20facilitate%20foreign%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcfo.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fcorporate-finance%2Fwhy-are-indias-fdi-inflows-slowing-down%2F108662947%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20termination%20of%20numerous%20bilateral%20investment%20treaties%20and%20a%20shift%20towards%20protectionist%20trade%20policies%20have%20further%20dampened%20investor%20sentiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEfforts%20to%20rectify%20these%20issues%20include%20recent%20trade%20agreements%20with%20Australia%2C%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20and%20the%20EFTA%20bloc.%20However%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20approach%20to%20negotiations%20remains%20cautious%2C%20with%20an%20emphasis%20on%20state%20control%20and%20limited%20exposure%20to%20foreign%20competition%2C%20said%20the%20business%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711456241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F01171239%2Findian-rupee-money-cash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fred-tape-low-labour-productivity-protectionist-policies-slowing-down-indias-fdi-flow%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Between%20April%20and%20September%20of%20last%20year%2C%20India%20received%20a%20little%20over%20%2410%20billion%20in%20FDI%20%E2%80%93%20the%20lowest%20tally%20for%20the%20first%20half%20of%20a%20financial%20year%20since%20the%202008%20global%20recession%2C%20according%20to%20RBI.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fred-tape-low-labour-productivity-protectionist-policies-slowing-down-indias-fdi-flow%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Telangana%3A%20Why%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Move%20to%20Appoint%20Chairs%20to%20State%20Entities%2C%20Form%20Caste%20Corporations%20Is%20Vital%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F29221132%2FEffect-4.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Telangana%20government%E2%80%99s%20move%20to%20appoint%20chairpersons%20to%2037%20corporations%2C%20or%20state-level%20entities%2C%20and%20other%20nominated%20posts%20was%20paused%20as%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20came%20into%20effect%20in%20the%20same%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20announced%20a%20list%20of%20selected%20chairpersons%20for%20the%2037%20entities%20on%20March%2016%2C%20the%20same%20day%20when%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Flok-sabha-election-schedule-2024-voting-to-start-on-april-19-counting-on-june-4%5C%22%3Eelection%20dates%20%3C%2Fa%3Efor%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20were%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20the%20process%20was%20halted%20even%20before%20individual%20orders%20to%20each%20selected%20chairperson%20were%20issued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20yet%20another%20setback%2C%20albeit%20temporarily%2C%20to%20an%20ambitious%20programme%20of%20the%20Congress%20government%20which%20would%20have%20placed%20senior%20party%20leaders%2C%20who%20were%20denied%20poll%20tickets%2C%20in%20several%20caste-based%20corporations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20programme%20to%20set%20up%20finance%20corporations%20for%2017%20caste%20groups%2C%20many%20of%20which%20belong%20to%20backward%20classes%2C%20also%20suffered%20a%20setback.%20These%20were%20in%20addition%20to%20the%2015%20other%20caste-based%20finance%20corporations%20already%20in%20existence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cabinet%20had%20announced%20the%20establishment%20of%2017%20corporations%20much%20earlier%20to%20the%20release%20of%20the%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20initiative%20is%20significant%20because%20this%20is%20the%20first%20time%20so%20many%20castes%20groups%20are%20getting%20finance%20corporations.%20Earlier%2C%20these%20castes%20used%20to%20get%20loans%20from%20umbrella%20organisations%20such%20as%20BC%20Corporation%20or%20SC%20Corporation.%20But%20now%2C%20individual%20castes%20have%20got%20their%20own%20finance%20corporations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20code%20also%20brought%20to%20a%20standstill%20a%20caste%20survey%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhyderabad%2Ftelangana-house-passes-resolution-on-caste-census%2Farticleshow%2F107764471.cms%5C%22%3Eproposed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20taken%20up%20in%20the%20state%20to%20identify%20the%20socioeconomic%20and%20educational%20standards%20of%20various%20sections.%20On%20February%2016%2C%20the%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhyderabad%2Ftelangana-house-passes-resolution-on-caste-census%2Farticleshow%2F107764471.cms%5C%22%3Epassed%20a%20resolution%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20caste%20census%20in%20the%20assembly%20and%20allotted%20Rs%20150%20crore%20for%20the%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20significance%20of%20the%20initiatives%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20three%20initiatives%2C%20the%20appointment%20of%20chairpersons%20for%2037%20corporations%20was%20a%20significant%20move%20by%20the%20Congress%20government%20to%20reward%20its%20cadre%20after%20winning%20the%20assembly%20elections.%20Nominating%20individuals%20to%20these%20corporations%20serves%20as%20a%20crucial%20mechanism%20to%20rehabilitate%20middle%20and%20grassroots-level%20workers%20of%20any%20ruling%20party%20who%20could%20not%20contest%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20previous%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samiti%20(BRS)%20regime%20had%20neglected%20this%20issue%20and%20as%20a%20result%2C%20many%20of%20its%20cadres%20were%20disappointed.%20The%20BRS%20workers%E2%80%99%20frustration%20is%20evident%20through%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Felections%2Flok-sabha%2Findia%2Fblow-to-brs-in-telangana-sitting-mp-mla-resign-from-party-join-congress-ahead-of-ls-polls%2Farticleshow%2F108562044.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Eresignations%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Ftelangana%2Fstory%2Franjith-reddy-another-mp-kcrs-party-resigns-lok-sabha-polls-likely-join-congress-2515960-2024-03-17%5C%22%3Efrom%20the%20party.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20former%20chairman%2C%20who%20did%20not%20want%20to%20be%20named%2C%20said%20the%20BRS%20(then%20Telangana%20Rashtra%20Samithi)%20came%20to%20power%20in%202014%20but%20he%20got%20the%20post%20only%20in%202021%2C%20despite%20him%20being%20with%20the%20party%20since%20its%20inception%20in%202001.%20He%20said%20he%20had%20also%20spent%20considerable%20money%20from%20his%20pocket%20on%20the%20party%20programmes.%20He%20further%20said%20that%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20chairpersons%20like%20Gyadari%20Balamallu%20of%20Telangana%20State%20Industrial%20Infrastructure%20Corporation%20(TSIIC)%20survived%20in%20these%20posts%20for%20extended%20periods%20with%20the%20blessings%20of%20then%20chief%20minister%20K.%20Chandrashekar%20Rao.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBalamallu%20served%20the%20longest%20tenure%20in%20the%20post%20in%20the%20BRS%20government%2C%20holding%20it%20for%20seven%20years%20until%20his%20resignation%20after%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20defeat%20in%20the%20assembly%20polls.%20But%2C%20he%20was%20also%20appointed%20to%20TSIIC%20two%20years%20after%20the%20government%20was%20sworn%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%20to%20that%2C%20the%20Congress%20announced%20the%20appointments%20of%20its%20workers%20much%20earlier.%20It%20allocated%20the%20chairman%20post%20to%20lesser-known%20bodies%20such%20as%20Telangana%20State%20Oilseeds%20Growers%20Federation%2C%20Minimum%20Wages%20Advisory%20Board%20and%20Telangana%20Foods.%20The%20castes%20of%20the%20appointed%20persons%20were%20also%20disclosed%20in%20the%20list%20to%20ensure%20transparency%20in%20representation%20across%20all%20sections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20a%20cabinet%20meeting%2C%20chaired%20by%20chief%20minister%20A.%20Revanth%20Reddy%2C%20had%20sanctioned%20finance%20corporations%20to%2017%20caste%20groups%20belonging%20to%20backward%20classes%2C%20Scheduled%20Castes%2C%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20and%20forward%20castes%20like%20Reddy%2C%20Vaishya%20and%20Kamma.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20announcement%20of%20a%20special%20welfare%20board%20for%20the%20economically%20backward%20classes%20was%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20announcements%20were%20made%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20existing%20finance%20corporations%20and%20federations%20of%20cooperative%20societies%20for%20backward%20class%20communities%20identified%20by%20their%20trades%20like%20goldsmiths%2C%20potters%2C%20toddy%20tappers%2C%20washermen%2C%20barbers%2C%20construction%20workers%2C%20bead%20vendors%2C%20bamboo%20artisans%20and%20stone%20cutters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20corporation%20for%20backward%20classes%20and%20a%20separate%20one%20for%20the%20most%20backward%20classes%20(MBCs)%20existed%20even%20during%20the%20BRS%20government.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20confined%20to%20paper.%20The%20corporations%20lacked%20powers%20and%20funds.%20Even%20their%20staff%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20being%20paid%20salaries%20regularly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BRS%20government%20had%20started%20corporations%20for%20Muslim%20minorities%2C%20Christians%20and%20Brahmins%20beside%20SCs%20and%20STs%20but%20they%20too%20lacked%20adequate%20supervision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20the%20assembly%20elections%2C%20the%20Congress%20had%20promised%20that%20it%20would%20set%20up%20finance%20corporations%20for%20all%20castes%20belonging%20to%20backward%20classes%20for%20their%20comprehensive%20development.%20It%20had%20also%20promised%20interest%20and%20security%20free%20loans%20of%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20for%20youngsters%20belonging%20to%20backward%20classes%20to%20start%20small%20trades.%20The%20promises%20were%20incorporated%20in%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20manifesto%20for%20the%20assembly%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandrashekar%20Rao%20had%20often%20promised%20that%20his%20government%20would%20strengthen%20the%20corporation%20for%20MBCs%20with%20a%20Rs%201%2C000%20crore%20budget.%20However%2C%20these%20corporations%20hardly%20got%20anything%20from%20the%20BRS%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chairman%20of%20State%20Backward%20Classes%20Commission%20V.%20Krishna%20Mohan%20Rao%20said%20the%20demand%20for%20caste-based%20finance%20corporations%20was%20long-pending.%20The%20establishment%20of%20these%20corporations%20won%E2%80%99t%20make%20sense%20if%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20strive%20to%20extend%20economic%20support%20schemes%20that%20improved%20the%20living%20standards%20of%20the%20beneficiaries.%20He%20also%20suggested%20that%20the%20support%20should%20help%20people%20repay%20their%20loans%20and%20not%20come%20in%20the%20form%20of%20freebies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20BRS%20activist%20and%20a%20former%20member%20of%20State%20BC%20Commission%2C%20E.%20Anjaneya%20Goud%2C%20said%20the%20BC%20corporation%20was%20the%20funding%20agency%20for%20all%20cooperative%20societies%20under%20the%20BRS%20government.%20Emphasising%20on%20the%20significant%20impact%20these%20corporations%20had%2C%20he%20said%20that%20the%20cooperative%20societies%20for%20sheep%20rearing%20and%20fisheries%20in%20irrigation%20tanks%20generated%20huge%20wealth%20for%20village%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711454414000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F29221132%2FEffect-4.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftelangana-why-congresss-move-to-appoint-chairs-to-state-entities-form-caste-corporations-is-vital%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22These%20moves%2C%20including%20a%20caste%20survey%2C%20were%20halted%20due%20to%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20coming%20into%20force.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftelangana-why-congresss-move-to-appoint-chairs-to-state-entities-form-caste-corporations-is-vital%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rebuilding%20Baltimore%20bridge%20could%20cost%20more%20than%20%24600m%20as%20closure%20to%20have%20trade%20implications%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711453140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F03%2F768x432%2Fskynews-francis-scott-key-bridge_6501361.jpg%3F20240326115244%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fbaltimore-trade-implications-from-francis-scott-key-bridge-collapse-as-rebuild-could-cost-600m-13102108%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20collapse%20of%20the%20Baltimore%20bridge%20has%20trade%20implications%2C%20with%20the%20cost%20of%20rebuilding%20estimated%20to%20surpass%20%24600m%20(%C2%A3474.12m)%2C%20experts%20have%20told%20Sky%20News.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A333%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fbaltimore-trade-implications-from-francis-scott-key-bridge-collapse-as-rebuild-could-cost-600m-13102108%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fbaltimore-trade-implications-from-francis-scott-key-bridge-collapse-as-rebuild-could-cost-600m-13102108%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fbaltimore-trade-implications-from-francis-scott-key-bridge-collapse-as-rebuild-could-cost-600m-13102108%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Kisan%20Mazdoor%20Commission'%20to%20Look%20at%20Rising%20Challenges%20for%20Farmers%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F26152957%2FScreenshot-2024-03-20-at-8.07.12%25E2%2580%25AFAM.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20the%20run%20up%20to%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20the%20Press%20Club%2C%20New%20Delhi%20recently%20witnessed%20the%20launching%20of%20new%20commission%20%E2%80%93%20Kisan%20Mazdoor%20Commission%20(KMC)%20%E2%80%93%20to%20address%20the%20overall%20structural%20problems%20in%20agriculture.%20The%20objective%20of%20the%20KMC%20is%20to%20go%20%E2%80%9Cbeyond%20the%20recommendations%20of%20Swaminathan%20Commission%20in%20the%20light%20of%20challenges%20arising%20out%20of%20the%20growing%20corporate%20control%20on%20the%20supply%20of%20farm%20inputs%20resulting%20in%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20production%20for%20farmers%20and%20on%20the%20markets%20for%20agricultural%20produce%20leading%20to%20the%20loss%20of%20incomes%20from%20farming%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20commission%20came%20out%20of%20discussions%20held%20between%20experts%2C%20farmers%2C%20labour%20unions%20and%20farm%20workers%E2%80%99%20unions%20under%20the%20banner%20of%20%E2%80%98Nation%20for%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20and%20later%20morphed%20into%20KMC.%20This%20commission%2C%20unlike%20others%2C%20aims%20to%20bring%20workers%20and%20farmers%20themselves%20into%20the%20agro-policy%20discussions.%20Jagmohan%20Singh%20has%20been%20voted%20as%20the%20national%20convenor%2C%20while%20Vijoo%20Krishnan%2C%20Navsharan%20Kaur%2C%20Roma%20Malik%2C%20Dinesh%20Abrol%2C%20P.%20Sainath%2C%20Thomas%20Franco%20and%20Nikhil%20Dey%20will%20be%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20KMC%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Agenda%20for%202024%E2%80%99%20aims%20to%20study%20%E2%80%9Crising%20cost%20of%20production%2C%20income%20enhancement%2C%20trade%20and%20investment%20(WTO%20and%20FTAs)%2C%20rural%20credit%20and%20insurance%2C%20common%20pool%20resources%2C%20ecological%20challenge%2C%20food%20and%20nutrition%2C%20women%20farmers%20and%20rural%20non-farm%20enterprises%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20senior%20journalist%20and%20Ramon%20Magsaysay%20awardee%20Sainath%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CM.S.%20Swaminathan%E2%80%99s%20life%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20contribution%20(the%20Swaminathan%20report%20on%20MSP)%20is%20ridiculed%20and%20thrown%20out%2C%20and%20meanwhile%20he%20was%20given%20a%20Bharat%20Ratna.%20We%20also%20become%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20first%20country%20to%20use%20aerial%20drone%20warfare%20against%20farmers.%20We%20didn%E2%80%99t%20use%20this%20against%20the%20terrorist%20but%20against%20the%20farmers.%20Drones%20dropped%20tear%20gas%20canisters%20on%20peacefully%20protesting%20farmers.%20%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20on%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20movement%2C%20Sainath%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20package%20they%20(the%20Union%20government)%20offered%20was%20farm%20laws%20through%20the%20back%20door%2C%20it%20said%20we%20will%20expand%20MSP%20to%20five%20crops%2C%20but%20on%20paper%20it%E2%80%99s%2023%20crops%20already%20%E2%80%93%20if%20you%20go%20to%20five%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20reduction.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20if%20we%20look%20at%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20own%20household%20consumption%20survey%2C%20whose%20veracity%20I%20doubt%2C%20even%20those%20figures%20show%20us%20that%20farmers%E2%80%99%20incomes%20are%20lower%20than%20the%20rural%20average.%20That%20is%20why%20KMC%20its%20a%20platform%20with%20farmers%20and%20mazdoors%20in%20the%20forefront%2C%20I%20too%20am%20only%20member%20of%20the%20drafting%20committee.%20It%20is%20time%20to%20update%20and%20go%20beyond%20the%20Swaminathan%20Commission%20to%20address%20newer%20challenges%20like%20climate%20change%2C%20etc.%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20issues%20the%20KMC%20proposes%20to%20look%20into%20are%20the%20Electricity%20Amendment%20Act%2C%20policy%20on%20water%20which%20is%20a%20basic%20right%2C%20pension%20scheme%2C%20Forest%20Rights%20Act%20implementation%2C%20MGNREGA%20implementation%2C%20policies%20on%20fisheries%2C%20rain%20fed%20dry%20land%20agriculture%2C%20climate%20crisis%2C%20biodiversity%20loss%20and%20seed%20systems.%20The%20KMC%20is%20planning%20to%20hold%20special%20consultations%20on%20the%20subjects%20of%20land%20rights%20for%20women%20farmers%20including%20women%20agricultural%20workers%2C%20rights%20of%20rural%20labour%20which%20will%20include%20all%20the%20basic%20rights%20(not%20just%20wages%20but%20access%20to%20capabilities%20and%20markets)%2C%20and%20the%20connections%20between%20agrarian%20crisis%2C%20environmental%20degradation%20and%20climate%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavsharan%20Kaur%20whose%20is%20leading%20the%20research%20on%20women%20within%20the%20KMC%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWomen%20are%20highly%20disadvantaged%20in%20agriculture.%20Despite%20being%20about%2060%25%20of%20the%20workforce%2C%20women%20barely%20own%20any%20land%20and%20in%20most%20places%20are%20not%20even%20counted%20as%20farmers.%20Even%20when%20we%20look%20the%20PM%20Kisan%20scheme%2C%20it%20hardly%20has%20any%20women%20beneficiaries.%20Women%20hardly%20have%20access%20to%20resources%20in%20agriculture.%20KMC%20will%20attempt%20to%20bridge%20this%20inequality.%20Apart%20from%20getting%20women%E2%80%99s%20needs%20to%20the%20forefront%2C%20we%20hope%20to%20influence%20policy%20through%20which%20women%20get%20more%20access%20to%20land%20in%20the%20villages%20and%20to%20create%20food%20and%20vegetables%20areas%20for%20better%20nutrition.%20Unused%20land%20within%20the%20public%20sector%2C%20should%20be%20redistributed%20to%20poor%20and%20landless%20women%20instead%20of%20corporates.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKMC%20has%20also%20set%20up%20other%20working%20groups%20to%20tackle%20the%20issues%20of%20%E2%80%9CAnalysis%20of%20Cost%20of%20Production%20and%20Income%20Sources%3B%20Analysis%20of%20Public%20%26amp%3B%20Private%20Investments%3B%20Farming%20Systems%3B%20Agricultural%20R%20%26amp%3B%20D%3B%20Agri-Digitalization%3B%20Rural%20Labour%3B%20Nutrition%20%26amp%3B%20Food%20Safety%3B%20Commons%3B%20Trade%20%26amp%3B%20Investment%3B%20Credit%20%26amp%3B%20Insurance.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDinesh%20Abrol%20also%20addressed%20the%20press%20conference%20and%20spoke%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%20He%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20root%20cause%20of%20the%20agrarian%20crisis%20is%20the%20capture%20of%20public%20sector%20institutions%20by%20domestic%20and%20foreign%20corporations%2C%20for%20example%20Amazon%2C%20a%20retailing%20company%2C%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fretail.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fe-commerce%2Fe-tailing%2Famazon-signs-pact-with-icar-to-empower-farmers-enrolled-under-kisan-store%2F100889478%5C%22%3Enow%20working%20with%3C%2Fa%3E%20Ministry%20of%20Agriculture%20on%20agriculture%20extension.%20How%20does%20this%20happen%3F%20Corporatisation%20of%20agriculture%20is%20happening%20at%20a%20very%20rapid%20pace.%20My%20own%20research%20on%20the%20Green%20Revolution%20shows%20this%2C%20because%20instead%20of%20scientific%20management%20and%20use%20of%20agri-inputs%2C%20now%20companies%20are%20pushing%20more%20chemicals%20and%20inputs%20to%20boost%20their%20business.%20This%20is%20huge%20cost%20for%20the%20farmers%20and%20ecology%20of%20the%20country.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711451700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F26152957%2FScreenshot-2024-03-20-at-8.07.12%25E2%2580%25AFAM.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fkisan-mazdoor-commission-to-look-at-rising-challenges-for-farmers-in-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20objective%20of%20the%20KMC%20is%20to%20go%20%E2%80%9Cbeyond%20the%20recommendations%20of%20Swaminathan%20Commission%20in%20the%20light%20of%20challenges%20arising%20out%20of%20the%20growing%20corporate%20control%20on%20the%20supply%20of%20farm%20inputs%20resulting%20in%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20production%20for%20farmers%20and%20on%20the%20markets%20for%20agricultural%20produce%20leading%20to%20the%20loss%20of%20incomes%20from%20farming%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fkisan-mazdoor-commission-to-look-at-rising-challenges-for-farmers-in-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Steven%20Spielberg%20warns%20of%20rising%20antisemitism%20and%20extremism%20in%20wake%20of%20Israel-Hamas%20war%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711450260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F03%2F768x432%2Fskynews-steven-spielberg-usc-shoa-foundation_6501157.jpg%3F20240326084910%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsteven-spielberg-warns-of-rising-antisemitism-and-extremism-in-wake-of-israel-hamas-war-13102080%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Steven%20S